def: Having no rival; without a competitor; peerless. [Spelt alsounrivalled.] Pope.
Either of two metameric nitrogenous hydrocarbon bases, C12H8N2,analogous to phenanthridine, but more highly nitrogenized.
The whole set of whorls of a spiral shell.
A state of profound insensibility from which it is difficult orimpossible to rouse a person. See Carus.
The quality of being acetous; sourness.
The quality or state of being isostemonous.
